## Analysis of the Main Target Image

The main target image shows two distinct structures on a dark checkered surface:

1. Left Structure:
   - 3 orange cylindrical blocks (block #6) arranged in an "L" shape: two vertical cylinders connected by one horizontal cylinder on top
   - 1 yellow half-cylindrical block (block #7) placed on top of the vertical orange cylinder
   - 1 yellow rectangular block (block #3) placed horizontally across the two vertical orange cylinders

2. Right Structure:
   - 1 orange cylindrical block (block #6) standing vertically
   - 3 orange triangular/wedge blocks (blocks #12, #14, and #15) arranged around the cylinder
   - 2 blue rectangular blocks (blocks #1 and #2) placed vertically on either side of the cylinder

Total block count: 11 blocks arranged in a multi-layered composition with various spatial relationships.

## Selected Blocks from the Dictionary

Based on the analysis, I need the following blocks from the dictionary:

- Block #1: Blue cube/rectangular block (used 1 time)
- Block #2: Blue rectangular block (used 1 time)
- Block #3: Yellow horizontal rectangular block (used 1 time)
- Block #6: Orange cylinder (used 4 times)
- Block #7: Yellow half-cylindrical block (used 1 time)
- Block #12: Orange triangular/wedge block (used 1 time)
- Block #14: Orange triangular/wedge block (used 1 time)
- Block #15: Orange triangular/wedge block (used 1 time)
